      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DURAN RACHEL (5) was sent out long odds last time but charged out of the boxes with a fast early sectional and gave a sight before being swallowed up late, finishing a 2.75 lengths fourth (17.90) over 305m at this track. Has ability and looks hard to stop. CADILLAC MAGIC (4) made light work of the tricky draw with a fast early sectional but gathered in and had to settle for the minors, finishing third (17.92) at this track over 305m. Expected to be in this for a long way. CADILLAC LANDAU (1) was safely held last time out, finishing fifth at this track over 305m behind One More Button (18.04) in a Grade 4/5. Can do much better this time. BLUE TO BURN (2) is a last-start placegetter in good time - solid claims again.",
